[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpyl24epqq[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow was detected by AddressSanitizer in the `mg_json_get` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction of the Mongoose JSON parser. During a libFuzzer run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“fuzz” target, [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a one‐byte write overflowed the local `nesting` array in `json.c` at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m. The crash occurred when the fuzz target parsed a specially crafted [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtestcase, resulting in an invalid write to the stack and an immediate abort.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer invoked the entry point `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` defined in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test/fuzz.c`, which in turn calls `mg_json_get` in `src/mongoose/src/json.c`. [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer flagged a stack‐buffer overflow inside `mg_json_get` when handling[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcertain input patterns.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a stack-buffer-overflow: a write beyond the bounds of a fixed-size array [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the stack.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow happens in the local array `nesting` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeclared at line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m of [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. An out‐of‐bounds index of [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mone byte past the end[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is written at line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The ASan report pinpoints the write in `mg_json_get` and shows that the invalid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess is in the same stack frame.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The failure surface is triggered via the fuzz harness in [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m81[0m[39m of `fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Affected code areas for investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • src/mongoose/src/json.c – especially the implementation of `mg_json_get`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling of nesting levels, index calculations, and boundary checks on the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` array.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c – the fuzzing harness that prepares inputs and calls [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto the JSON API, to understand how inputs drive parser state.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important findings  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash reproducibly occurs on libFuzzer’s [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m-run experiment with the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovided `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • All relevant metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASan shadow bytes, stack trace, frame information[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirms the overflow is in the parser function, not in the harness or external [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibraries.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root‐cause analysis or remedies are provided here; the focus is on the nature of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow, its location in the code, and the affected components for a complete [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvestigation.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray in mg_json_get.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is used for parser depth checks.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Because the code checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before pushing into [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, depths in the range [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m..[0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m][0m[39m pass that check but overflow the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m‐entry array.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Critical Logic to Preserve  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must continue to enforce a maximum parse depth.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The push into the `nesting` array with `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` must never exceed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mits bounds.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other parser behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath-matching logic, token consumption, error codes[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be altered.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Strategy  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Use the correct constant—MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH—for the in-bounds checks [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately before writing into `nesting`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In `src/mongoose/src/json.c`, locate the two blocks that handle [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m~[0m[1;36m166[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m174[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m175[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Replace:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This change ensures that `depth` never becomes equal to or greater than the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray size, preventing any out-of-bounds write.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Optionally [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrecommended for maintainability[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add a `static_assert` in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/mongoose/src/json.h` to guarantee at compile time that the two constants stay [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min sync or that `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING <= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`. For example:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #if MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING > MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     # error [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING must not exceed MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Do not modify any fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest/fuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or external libraries. No [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests or other code paths are touched.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Safety**: By switching to `>= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, we assert before the push [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the `nesting` array has room, eliminating the overflow.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Minimal impact**: Only two boundary‐check lines are changed. All other [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser logic, including path matching and token handling, remains identical.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **API stability**: This does not alter public APIs or default behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexcept[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimiting JSON nesting to the array size, which it always was intended to[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Maintainability**: Adding a compile‐time assert prevents future drift [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbetween the two constants.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - JSON inputs with nesting deeper than `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` will now return [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` at depth [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m instead of [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m. If deeper nesting support is desired,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe user can override `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` at build time to a higher value, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mautomatically affecting the bound check.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The optional `static_assert` ensures that any future configuration mismatch is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaught at compile time rather than causing a runtime overflow.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Validation  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the library and rerun AddressSanitizer + libFuzzer. The previous [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow should no longer occur, and valid JSON inputs within [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlevels continue to parse normally.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm no new sanitizer warnings or test failures are introduced.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations from the sanitizer output:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The array `nesting` is allocated on the stack, and an index equal to its length [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is written to, causing the overflow.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens under a certain JSON input path that triggers deep or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed nesting.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe submitted patch makes two changes in `src/json.c`:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--- a/src/json.c[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-173[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m173[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand adds in `src/json.h`:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+#endif[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+#if MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING > MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+# error [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING must not exceed MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m #endif[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The intent was to tighten the check from “greater than” to “greater than or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequal,” and enforce at compile time that `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` does not exceed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Test Log After Patch[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The same fuzz run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still produces the identical AddressSanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow remains on the `nesting` array at the same offset [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, showing that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch did not prevent writing out of bounds.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand and fully address this overflow, the following parts of the codebase [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be reviewed:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Declaration of the `nesting` array** in `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m131[0m[39m of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm its size relative to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Investigate how the code increments and indexes into `nesting`.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Depth-tracking logic** around lines [0m[1;36m160[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m190[0m[39m in `src/json.c`:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `depth` is incremented/decremented as `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, and `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` are [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessed.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether checks exist before every write to `nesting` or related arrays.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Definitions of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`** in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/json.h`:  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the macros match the intended maximum levels of nesting.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that they are used consistently in both code and array declarations.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Path parsing logic** that may write additional state into the `nesting` array [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor related buffers, especially in cases of malformed or deeply nested JSON.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`test/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** only as needed to reproduce the issue; the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause lies in `mg_json_get`, not the harness itself.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic fix will likely involve adjusting the size of the `nesting` buffer or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmore carefully bounding all indexing operations against its actual capacity.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:166[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m174[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The function mg_json_get declares a stack array `unsigned char [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault size [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but uses the separate macro [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in its bounds checks. This mismatch allows [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth` to grow past the actual array length, leading to a one‐byte overflow when [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth == MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The previous patch attempted to tighten the check to `depth >= [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` but left the two‐macro design in place.  Because [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` remain out of sync, and because [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompile‐time enforcement of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING <= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` was [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich would error out unless upstream build flags changed one macro[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow wasn’t reliably prevented.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Unify the notion of “maximum JSON nesting depth” into a single macro, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, which:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Controls the size of the `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` array.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Governs all depth‐overflow checks at runtime.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminates the separate `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` macro to remove confusion.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step‐by‐Step Patch Plan[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Refactor `src/json.h`[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove or collapse the `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` definition entirely.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Retain only one macro, `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, for maximum nesting.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```diff[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         --- a/src/json.h[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         +++ b/src/json.h[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         @@[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - #endif[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         -[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - #if MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING > MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - # error [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING must not exceed MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         - #endif[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m If backward compatibility is needed where other code refers to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, add:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```c[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         but this alias is purely cosmetic and not required in the JSON parser [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Update `src/json.c`—use a single macro for both array size and bound checks.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. At the top of `mg_json_get`, ensure the array matches the sole macro:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```c[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* before: unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m; *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNo change needed here if `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` remains its original name.[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace both occurrences of the depth‐check to guard against writing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the array—compare to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` using `>=`:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```diff[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         --- a/src/json.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         +++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         @@ [0m[1;36m-164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         -    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         +    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing logic[0m[33m...[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         @@ [0m[1;36m-175[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m175[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         -    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         +    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing logic[0m[33m...[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. No other references to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` should remain in the JSON [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The JSON‐parsing FSM [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstate‐machine for `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, commas, colons, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39metc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains untouched. Only the depth‐overflow guard changes.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` stays at its default [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unless the integrator overrides [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit. The behavior for normal and malformed JSON under shallow nesting is preserved.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer harness and tests are unmodified, ensuring that existing test coverage [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues to exercise the same code paths.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Why This Works[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By having a single authoritative macro for both buffer size and overflow [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks, we guarantee that `depth` never attains the array’s length or beyond.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All increments [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are now shielded by `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and will return `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` before any illegal write.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminating `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` removes the risk of drift between two [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelated constants.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any external code or build system relied on `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` being [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindependently configurable, they must now override `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` only. Any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempt to define `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` will no longer have effect.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack usage remains bounded by `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`; if integrators need deeper[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting support, they can raise `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` at compile time [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., via [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-[0m[33mDMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Testing[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the library and re‐run the fuzz target under AddressSanitizer for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m≥[0m[1;36m10000[0m[39m iterations to confirm the one‐byte overflow no longer occurs.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit tests for JSON extraction to ensure no regressions in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuccessful lookups or error codes.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNo harness or test code modifications are required; the fix is entirely [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontained in `src/json.h` and `src/json.c`.[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `mg_json_get` function in `mongoose/src/json.c`. The sanitizer detected a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte stack-buffer-overflow in the local array `nesting` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at line [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m. The initial code used two macros—`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for array sizing and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for depth checks—allowing `depth` to exceed the buffer’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapacity.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was applied that removed `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` from `src/json.h` and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanged both overflow checks in `json.c` from[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor both `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` cases. After recompilation, the fuzzer still triggers the same[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer invocation triggered AddressSanitizer during a call to `mg_json_get` in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mongoose/src/json.c`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error report shows a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at an address within a stack frame’s [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` array:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `nesting` covers bytes `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes total[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, just past the end of `nesting`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack:  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `mg_json_get` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → libFuzzer internals → `main`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow arises before any custom unwind mechanisms; ASan is confident it’s a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrue stack overflow.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `src/json.h`, the `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` definition was removed, leaving only:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `src/json.c`, both checks guarding increases of `depth` were changed from [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musing `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to testing against `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`:  [0m               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   + if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   applied in the branches for `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mobject[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39marray[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer log after patch still reports:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: stack-buffer-overflow [0m[33m...[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m in mg_json_get [0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m186:28[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m246[0m[39m:        break;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m248[0m[39m:      case S_COMMA_OR_EOO:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m249[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth <= [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m250[0m[39m:          return MG_JSON_INVALID;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
