[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[39m:          expecting = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? S_KEY : S_VALUE;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m253[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'[0m[32m}[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m254[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && c == [0m[32m'[0m[32m}[0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m255[0m[39m:            return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m256[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && c == [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m','[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m257[0m[39m:            return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m258[0m[39m:          [0m[1;35mMG_EOO[0m[1;39m([0m[32m'O'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m259[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && ei >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ci++;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m260[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Review and Correct All Guards on `depth` Before Incrementing:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure every location that writes `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[33m...[0m[39m` is preceded by a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We have two such branches [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m` and `[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but a third implicit “default” or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother parsing branches may also push onto `nesting`. We must audit the entire [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing loop in `mg_json_get` to locate **any** additional `depth++` or writes to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Audit the Entire `mg_json_get` Function:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fetch and review lines [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m260[0m[39m of `src/json.c`, focusing on:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m All occurrences of `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor any write to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Any other increments to `depth` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in error conditions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm no code path bypasses the guard we standardized.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Synchronize `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` Usage:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any residual references to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.h`, keep only:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, apply:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     immediately **before** every line of the form `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[33m...[0m[39m`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify Matching Buffer Allocation:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` remains unchanged.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This buffer holds exactly `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` entries, so valid indices are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[39m..MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH-[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Add Optional Defensive Fallback:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the parsing loop but before any use of `nesting`, assert or double‐check[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `depth <= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`. This is a no-op in release builds [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mMG_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth <= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but triggers in debug builds if our [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards missed any paths.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Regression Testing:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run libFuzzer harness to confirm no stack-buffer-overflow.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a small targeted unit test that crafts a deeply nested JSON [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth = [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH exactly[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, asserting it returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` and does not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm existing tests for JSON parsing still pass.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow persists because one or more `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` operations lack the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated guard. Correcting every push to `nesting` ensures no out‐of‐bounds write.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using a single macro [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m avoids mismatches. The `>=` check [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents writing at index equal to the buffer size.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A defensive assertion guards against future code changes introducing new push [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No fuzz harness or external code is modified; functionality remains intact and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests unbroken.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>src/json.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m260[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the function `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when parsing deeply nested JSON. The [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow writes beyond the bounds of the local array `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`. A patch was [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted: the macro `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` was removed from json.h, and the code in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjson.c was modified to use checks against `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` before pushing onto [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when encountering `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` tokens. After rebuilding and rerunning the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer, the same stack-buffer-overflow at the same location reoccurred, indicating [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch did not prevent out-of-bounds writes to the `nesting` buffer.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m feeds arbitrary input to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a one-byte write beyond the end of the local array [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` in `mg_json_get` at json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace shows the overflow happens while `mg_json_get` is iterating through[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJSON characters, updating `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` without guaranteeing `depth < [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The local array is declared in json.c around line [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m; the violation occurs at [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of a buffer sized for [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m or fewer entries.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.h`, the preprocessor block defining `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` was [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved entirely.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, all comparisons `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` were replaced[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and duplicate checks were added before each[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` on seeing `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` remains set to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m in json.h; code paths now bail out earlier [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code compiles and the fuzzer run completes but still triggers the exact same [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer error at json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that either the macro checks do not align with the actual size of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, or there are code paths where `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is still reached when[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth` equals the buffer’s limit.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Definition and size of the `nesting` array in `json.c` versus the constants [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and the removed `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. Confirm whether the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbacking buffer size matches the new limit.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All control flow paths in `mg_json_get` that modify `depth` and write to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`—ensure every path enforces a strict upper bound before the write.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Handling of the variables `ed`, `ci`, `ei`, and `pos` in relation to `depth`, to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverify there are no off-by-one or logic branches that skip the new checks.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between macro definitions in json.h and code in json.c: make sure the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoval of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` does not leave any uses of it or default to an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munintended value.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Unify and correct the nesting‐bounds logic  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the redundant MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING macro entirely from src/json.h.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rely solely on MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH for both the size of the `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand all depth‐limit checks.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Update the nesting buffer declaration  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In src/json.c, confirm `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` remains. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis ensures the array and the depth‐limit constant agree.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Simplify and harden the depth‐check in the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` handlers  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove all remaining references to MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING in json.c.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the existing pair of checks around `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` with a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle, canonical check immediately before that line:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do this in both the object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`c == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`c == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m branches.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Drop any extra `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or duplicate `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guards; one [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck is both necessary and sufficient.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify no other code paths write to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` without the new guard  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Search for any other `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` usages [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in different switch [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases or utility functions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Apply the same single check before each occurrence.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Remove MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING from the header  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In src/json.h, delete lines defining MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING. The header now only [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeds:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Add a compile‐time assert  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the declaration of `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, include a static assertion to guard [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst future mismatches:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35m_Static_assert[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH,[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[32m"nesting[0m[32m[[0m[32m][0m[32m size must match MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExplanation and Rationale  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash was caused by a macro mismatch: `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` was sized by [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but bounds were tested against MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowing up to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m writes into a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte buffer.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By eliminating MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING and using only MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH, we restore a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m1:1[0m[39m relationship between the buffer’s size and its guard checks.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Consolidating to one check directly above the write makes it impossible to forget[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor misapply a guard.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This preserves existing parser logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth, ed, ci/ei, pos updates[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and only [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterposes the minimal necessary bound check.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Side Effects: JSON inputs nested deeper than [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m levels will now return [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_TOO_DEEP early—identical to the original intent of capping nesting.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No changes to harness code or external libraries are required, so existing tests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand fuzzing logic remain valid.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A similar pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39msingle‐check before buffer write[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is already used elsewhere in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in MG_EOO macros decrementing depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so this follows established [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstyle.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer run of the `mg_json_get` function in `mongoose/src/json.c` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproduced a stack-buffer-overflow when invoked via the fuzz harness. The buffer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` was overwritten at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m. A patch [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas applied, removing an unused `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` constant, adding a static [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massertion on the size of `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, and tightening depth checks to `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-running the fuzzer, the same one-byte write overflow at the same stack offset [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecurred, indicating the patch did not prevent the out-of-bounds write.[0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzing run with AddressSanitizer detected a stack-buffer-overflow in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The bad write was size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m to a stack array `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, at an offset of [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m beyond [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe array’s upper bound.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failing frame shows `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` defined as [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m in `json.h`, so valid indices are `[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m`, but [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode writes at index [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer report shows the overflow occurs while processing an input in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` invoked by the fuzz driver.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations from the log:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overflow offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m-byte stack array.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash consistently in `mg_json_get` path logic.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer call stack: `mg_json_get` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → libFuzzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternals.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.h`, removed `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and left only `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mset to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, directly under the declaration of `unsigned char [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`, inserted:  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35m_Static_assert[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH,  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[32m"nesting[0m[32m[[0m[32m][0m[32m size must match MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed two depth checks from `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >=[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`—once for `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and once for `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other code was altered.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult After Patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer was rerun with the same test harness and yielded an identical [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer overflow at the same source location and offset.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The static assertion passed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso `nesting` is correctly sized[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the runtime [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic still allows writes past index [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m, up to index [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The loop and indexing logic in `mg_json_get` around lines [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/json.c`, specifically how `depth` is incremented and how elements of [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` are accessed and updated.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The relationship between `depth`, `ed`, `ci`, `ei`, and how these control writes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto the `nesting` array.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any remaining references to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` or implicit assumptions about [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum nesting depth elsewhere in the module.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The path‐parsing logic in the fuzz target [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`test/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand what JSON[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths are being fed into `mg_json_get`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definitions and use of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` in `src/json.h` to verify [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistency with the implementation.[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:149[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m158[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m In the ascii table, the distance between `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Ditto for `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`. Hence +[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m in the code below.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m151[0m[39m:#define [0m[1;35mMG_EOO[0m[1;39m([0m[39mx[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m                                            \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m152[0m[39m:  do [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m                                                       \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m153[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && ci != ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND;   \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m154[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc != nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m + [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_INVALID; \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:    depth--;                                                 \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mMG_CHECKRET[0m[1;39m([0m[39mx[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;                                          \[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m157[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m158[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local array `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is being [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindexed by `depth` when pushing [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m or [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m tokens via `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The depth‐limit checks in these branches must use `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould trigger before any out‐of‐bounds write.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The last patch updated only the two checks in the `[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m` and `[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m` cases. [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the fuzzer log shows that writes continued up to index [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, implying:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Either some other code path writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` without a proper depth [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbound check.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m The patched checks were not guarding *all* increment sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code path that resets `ei`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`ci` or treats closing braces might repush[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must audit the entire function to find *every* increment of `depth` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mevery [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite into `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and ensure a guard `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;` precedes it.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Inspect All `depth++` Sites[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two known sites:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • In the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` case: `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m;`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • In the `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` case: `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m;`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm there is no other hidden push [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in a default or error‐handling [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that no code after a matching‐end macro `MG_EOO` repushes.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implement Comprehensive Depth Guards[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In both `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` cases, place the check *immediately before* the write:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any stale references or definitions of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`; rely [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msolely on `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a single `[0m[1;35massert[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` or `_Static_assert` to ensure no off‐by‐one:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35m_Static_assert[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH must be positive"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Optionally, to be defensive, add an `MG_CHECK_RET`‐style wrapper or inline [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     static int [0m[1;35mpush_nesting[0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned char *a, int *depth, unsigned char c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m*depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       a[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     And replace both direct writes with `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpush_nesting[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting, &depth, c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m != [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validate Closing‐Brace Logic[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `MG_EOO` macro reads `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`; ensure that on every decrement [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`depth--`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m depth cannot go negative or skip the guard.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that after closing, no residual writes still bypass guard.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Test & Regression[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run AddressSanitizer fuzz harness to ensure no stack‐buffer overflow at any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack offset.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit tests to verify no regressions; the logic and return codes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor deep paths remain unchanged.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a small unit test that feeds an excessively nested JSON path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` is returned and no overflow [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Justification and Preservation of Functionality[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach directly addresses the buffer‐overflow by guarding *every* write[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, preventing depth from exceeding its capacity.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It preserves the existing logic: when depth ≤ valid range, tokens are still [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecorded in `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, and path resolution proceeds.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error‐return behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains in line with existing error[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodes.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By removing `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, we eliminate confusion and ensure a single [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mauthoritative limit.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance: the extra branch per push is negligible considering JSON parsing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcost.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Correctness: no broader utility or harness code is modified; only the core [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser function is hardened.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintainability: centralized guard or inline function reduces duplication and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisk of missing future pushes.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
